narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Deeper understanding of the political foundations of American/western society
I developed an understanding of the moral, philosophical, and economic underpinnings of liberal and conservative thought from an historical and modern perspective.
I learned a ton about what it means to liberal and conservative, the nuances of the two ideologies, and where the foundational philosophies of each political philosophy came from

It was incredibly interesting to read some of the earliest conservative and liberal thinkers and learn the values that were typical of classical conservatism and liberalism. As we moved into thinkers of the modern period, it was fascinating to see which conservative and liberal values have endured time and which haven't. By taking this course, you'll get to discuss in-depth some of the most influential conservative and liberal thinkers throughout history, and Prof. Collins does a great job of putting thinkers into conversation with one another. This course also proved to be a helpful introduction to the French Revolution, which I had not yet studied up until this point, and highlighted the key tensions between supporters and detractors of the revolution. By the end of the course, I felt like I could confidently explain to someone what conservatism and liberalism are, how they have changed since their origin, and the merits and demerits of both.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Very engaging discussion and conversations based on reading

This course is great. The only weakness was the in-class debate, and this is only because I didnt really understand the format until it was time to debate. Other that that, discussions were always interesting.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if you are interested in political philosophy
Absolutely, I would recommend this course.
